The problem asks us to implement a function `MakeChain(input []Domino) ([]Domino, bool)` that finds a valid chain of dominoes from a given set.
A valid chain means:
- Adjacent dominoes match on their touching sides.
- The first and last sides of the chain match.
- All given dominoes must be used exactly once.
- Dominoes can be flipped (rotated).

This is essentially finding an Eulerian circuit in a multigraph where the numbers on the domino halves are nodes, and each domino is an edge between two nodes.
