- "square" -> i=0 's', i=1 'q', next 'u', i=3. 'a' break. split=3. "are" + "squ" + "ay" = "aresquay" ✓
- "my" -> i=0 'm', i=1 'y' (i>0) break. split=1. "y" + "m" + "ay" = "ymay" ✓
- "rhythm" -> i=0 'r', i=1 'h', i=2 'y' break. split=2. "ythm" + "rh" + "ay" = "ythmrhay" ✓
- "yellow" -> i=0 'y' (i=0, not break), i=1 'e' break. split=1. "ellow" + "y" + "ay" = "ellowyay" ✓ (Rule 1 says starts with vowel or xr/yt, yellow starts with y consonant sound, so rule 2 applies)
